   <abstract>Structure built in 1910. It was designed by George Barber in Colonial Revival style built of brick. It features a double high Ionic colonnade. It was first campus building to include steel supports and to have indoor plumbing. It is located at 502 E. Lamar Alexander Parkway, Maryville, TN.</abstract>
